{"title":"Match Your Axles to Your Hubs with Chris King x Robert Axle Project Thru Axles","link":"https://bikerumor.com/chris-king-x-robert-axle-project-thru-axles/","date":1698325200000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-looks-like-a-stem-cap.jpeg\" alt=\"Chris King and Robert Axle Project cusom colors looks like a stem cap\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-looks-like-a-stem-cap.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-looks-like-a-stem-cap-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-looks-like-a-stem-cap-800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-looks-like-a-stem-cap-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-looks-like-a-stem-cap-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-looks-like-a-stem-cap-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Vibrantly colored bike parts are the jam of Portland, Oregon’s Chris King Precision Components. Beautiful anodization has become almost synonymous with the brand’s identity. Now, they’ve teamed up with fellow Oregonians, Robert Axle Project to <a href=\"https://chrisking.com/products/king-thru-axle\">release thru-axles</a> that match some of Chris King’s iconic colors. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-two-sizes-e1698256002635.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"778\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-two-sizes-e1698256002635.jpeg\" alt=\"Chris King and Robert Axle Project cusom colors two sizes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-two-sizes-e1698256002635.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-two-sizes-e1698256002635-297x181.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-two-sizes-e1698256002635-800x486.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-two-sizes-e1698256002635-120x73.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-two-sizes-e1698256002635-768x467.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Photo c. Chis King Precision Components</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-hero-e1698256169464.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"782\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-hero-e1698256169464.jpeg\" alt=\"Chris King and Robert Axle Project cusom colors hero\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-hero-e1698256169464.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-hero-e1698256169464-297x181.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-hero-e1698256169464-800x489.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-hero-e1698256169464-120x73.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-hero-e1698256169464-768x469.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Robert Axle Project and Chirs King are producing a line of new axles that will work for drop or flat bar bikes. The selection will be available through Chris King’s website right now.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-three-in-a-row-e1698256109672.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"851\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-three-in-a-row-e1698256109672.jpeg\" alt=\"Chris King and Robert Axle Project cusom colors three in a row\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-three-in-a-row-e1698256109672.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-three-in-a-row-e1698256109672-297x197.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-three-in-a-row-e1698256109672-800x532.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-three-in-a-row-e1698256109672-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-three-in-a-row-e1698256109672-768x511.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-three-in-a-row-e1698256109672-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-in-a-line.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-in-a-line.jpeg\" alt=\"Chris King and Robert Axle Project cusom colors in a line\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-in-a-line.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-in-a-line-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-in-a-line-800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-in-a-line-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-in-a-line-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-in-a-line-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The first run of colors for the product launch will include 3D Violet, Matte Turquoise, and Black. Going forward, they’ll be adding more colors in the future. In an attempt to cover most of the bikes on the market, there will be 5 axles for bikes of the drop bar ilk (142×12 and 100×12) and five more for boost and super-boost mountain bikes. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Chris King Had This to Say</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Greg Hudson, King’s Sales Manager, said, “<em>We’re about making the best products possible in a responsible way and collaborating with people who feel the same. Robert Axle Project is an Oregon company, and these are high-quality axles, customized with end caps that match our iconic stem cap shape. Not only do they look good, but they’re also of exceptional quality and stiffness compared to other options available</em>“.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-rear-drop-out.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-rear-drop-out.jpeg\" alt=\"Chris King and Robert Axle Project cusom colors rear drop out\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-rear-drop-out.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-rear-drop-out-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-rear-drop-out-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-rear-drop-out-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-rear-drop-out-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-rear-drop-out-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-front-fork.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-front-fork.jpeg\" alt=\"Chris King and Robert Axle Project cusom colors front fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-front-fork.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-front-fork-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-front-fork-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-front-fork-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-front-fork-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-front-fork-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Hudson also stated that “<em>This is part of our effort to become the upgrade of choice for mass market, available-at-retail bikes too</em>.” Continuing, “<em>Many riders associate us with the handmade market, which we absolutely love, but our mission</em> <em>is to improve the ride of every bike our components grace. Our objective has always been to help bikes of all types last longer and ride better, which is also Robert Axle Project’s goal”.</em> </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-green-purple-e1698256308803.jpeg\"><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Chris-King-and-Robert-Axle-Project-cusom-colors-green-purple.jpeg\" alt=\"Chris King and Robert Axle Project cusom colors green purple\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, the caps will have that familiar and iconic curve of the Chis King headset. The newly available axles retail for $65 and are said to fit all Yetis, Santa Cruz, Pivots, Transitions, most handmade bikes, all ENVE forks, and more…</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://chrisking.com/\">ChrisKing.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/chris-king-x-robert-axle-project-thru-axles/\">Match Your Axles to Your Hubs with Chris King x Robert Axle Project Thru Axles</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d03b676bc7bf3649a54d4493ad8cc8c06b64c2edb475b1a8e36ac3db525675c5","category":"Cycling"}